lines.text: Jim, I want you to go away for my sake!
I won't drink with a man who robbed the orphans of the King's soldiers!
If you are an honest man, you may kiss me goodbye.

[on death of Nat-U-Rich]
Poor little mother!
Come out West where people keep their hands in their own pockets.
We're going to find Jim and bring him home.
Get a-goin', Bud, and don't stop to pick flowers!
I'm broke. Tell the boys I'll pay 'em somehow.
